EOS-SAR is a Python package that implements Kayrros' toolbox for Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) data ("EOS-SAR").

EOS-SAR is provided to the USER by Kayrros under the present license agreement (the "Agreement").


ARTICLE 1 – License Grant

Kayrros grants to USER a free, non-exclusive, non-transferable, worldwide license to access and use EOS-SAR solely for internal research purposes. The USER shall have the right to publish the results, in the USER's field of study, obtained through the use of EOS-SAR and other software. USER undertakes to mention Kayrros in any such publication.

The license does not include the right of USER to disclose or sublicense EOS-SAR or any part thereof, or otherwise to resell EOS-SAR to any third party. The license does not convey to USER any Intellectual Property rights.


ARTICLE 2 – Duration - Termination

This Agreement shall commence on the date of its last signature and continue until terminated by either Party upon fifteen (15) days prior written notice.

Termination of this Agreement shall not affect any rights or obligations which have accrued prior to the effective date of termination or that are intended by the parties to survive the termination or expiration of the Agreement.


ARTICLE 3 – Ownership

Title and ownership to EOS-SAR, shall at all times remain with Kayrros. For the avoidance of doubt, the USER has no right on Kayrros intellectual property, except as expressly permitted herein. Kayrros reserves the right to release EOS-SAR to any third party (including to the public) at any time under any conditions.


ARTICLE 4 – Warranty - Liability

No representation: EOS-SAR provided to USER by Kayrros is a creative work of the mind. EOS-SAR is provided "as is" and Kayrros disclaims and makes no representations or warranties expressed or implied in relation to EOS-SAR. USER accepts sole responsibility for its use of EOS-SAR.

Limitation of liability: In no event will Kayrros hereto be liable for any losses or damage, whether direct or indirect, special, incidental, consequential, exemplary, or punitive that may result from the use of EOS-SAR.


ARTICLE 5 – Entire Agreement

This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the USER and Kayrros and supersede all prior understandings and instruments in respect of the USER's use of EOS-SAR.


ARTICLE 6 – Governing law and jurisdiction

This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of France, without giving effect to any choice of law or conflict of law provisions. The USER consents to the exclusive jurisdiction and venue of the courts in the city of Paris.

